

# Design DropBox

## Clarify
### Requirement
1. Users should be able to upload and download their files/photos from any device.
2. Our service should support automatic synchronization between devices, i.e., after updating a file on one device, it should get synchronized on all devices.


### Design Considerations
1. save file in chunks (2mb - 4mb)
	- If a user fails to upload a file, then only the failing chunk will be retried.
	- if change the file on local, only need to update small chunk of file in storage, instead have another copy of the whole file
	- Allow multi-thread work on upload/download different part of chunk.

2. Use metadata file to document all the chunks information
	

## Service
### High level design

We need a block server to upload/download file from cloud storage. And a metadata service to get and put data from database. Synchronization Service handle the workflow of notifying all clients about different changes for synchronization.

![No Graph available](data:image/png;base64,)

### Client

1. Upload and download files.
2. Detect file changes in the workspace folder/Server.
3. Handle conflict due to offline or concurrent updates.

##### Client check for update

Constant pulling from server is not good, so we can use HTTP long pulling

#### Detail Design

I. **Internal Metadata Database** will keep track of all the files, chunks, their versions, and their location in the file system.

II. **Chunker** will split the files into smaller pieces called chunks. It will also be responsible for reconstructing a file from its chunks. Our chunking algorithm will detect the parts of the files that have been modified by the user and only transfer those parts to the Cloud Storage; this will save us bandwidth and synchronization time.

III. **Watcher** will monitor the local workspace folders and notify the Indexer (discussed below) of any action performed by the users, e.g. when users create, delete, or update files or folders. Watcher also listens to any changes happening on other clients that are broadcasted by Synchronization service.

IV. **Indexer** will process the events received from the Watcher and update the internal metadata database with information about the chunks of the modified files. Once the chunks are successfully submitted/downloaded to the Cloud Storage, the Indexer will **communicate with the remote Synchronization Service** to broadcast changes to other clients and update remote metadata database.

![No Graph available](data:image/png;base64,)

### Synchronization Server

用来根据用户的upload, 通知并同步所有的client, 同时也同步client的internal metadata DB

同步(Synchronization)时候只传递两个version的不同的地方, 可以节省空间/时间



因为可以有很多client, 这样synchronization service很有可能会在短时间收到很多的request造成throttle. 所以可以在client和Synchronization service之间增加一个message queue(SQS or Kafka queue)





## Storage

### Metadata Storage

 maintaining the versioning and metadata information about files/chunks, users, and workspaces

User SQL as it has lock



Information in database:

1. Chunks
2. Files
3. User
4. Devices
5. Workspace (sync folders)



### Block Storage

Cloud storage



### WorkFlow

1. Client A uploads chunks to cloud storage.
2. Client A updates metadata and commits changes.
3. Client A gets confirmation and notifications are sent to Clients B and C about the changes.
4. Client B and C receive metadata changes and download updated chunks.

## Scale

### Data duplication

去除所有重复的chunk, 可以根据新chunk算hash然后跟旧的比较

**Post-process deduplication** 先存再算hash再删除, 缺点是占用空间(一小段时间) 占bandwidth, 因为data还是要upload

**In-line deduplication** 缺点是要在传送之前作比较, 浪费时间
